  "_alias_comment": "Ordered class-prefix rules. Real modification names from siRNAmod/HelixZero are compositional (<modification-class><base>, e.g. \"2'-O-Methyluridine\"). We map by modification CLASS to a single symbol regardless of the underlying base, matching the paper's 30-symbol scheme. Rules are tested IN ORDER (first match wins) against the lowercased name with apostrophes normalized; more specific / higher-priority classes come first. Sugar modifications take precedence over backbone (phosphorothioate) when both are present, because the per-position symbol describes the nucleotide.",
  "alias_rules": [
    { "match": "unlocked nucleic acid",  "symbol": "6", "note": "UNA (check before 'locked')" },
    { "match": "alfa-l-locked nucleic acid", "symbol": "L", "note": "alpha-L-LNA" },
    { "match": "locked nucleic acid",    "symbol": "L", "note": "LNA family (incl. ENA/cET variants)" },
    { "match": "2-o-methyl",             "symbol": "M", "note": "2'-O-Methyl (incl. -3'-PS combos)" },
